cs.LG, cs.HC, cs.NE, cs.CV, cs.AI 

The paper proposes a deep learning approach using convolutional neural networks (CNNs) for EEG-based emotion recognition, which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG) and human-computer interaction (cs.HC). The use of brain connectivity features and asymmetric brain activity patterns suggests a focus on neuroscience (cs.NE). The use of CNNs also suggests a focus on computer vision (cs.CV) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI).
